ee these principles retained. Nevertheless, it should be noted that the UK has won a greater share of EU space research grants and infrastructure and service contracts thus far than it has invested by virtue of its membership of the EU, suggesting that the UK fares well out of both ESA’s and the EU’s procurement processes</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 39.6pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-21.6pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">1.2.</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ESA has changed considerably over the last decade</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> ESA has developed world-class skills and competences that must be retained and utilised.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">It has</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> broadened its horizons from a s</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">cientific R&amp;D organisation into one that also ha</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">s a strong focus on supporting i</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ndustry. Especially through its ARTES </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">t</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">elecommunications </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">p</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">rogrammes</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">,</span><span 